@node Via manual @samp{git clone} and @code{load-path}
@section Via manual @samp{git clone} and @code{load-path}

Clone the Git repository.

@example
git clone https://codeberg.org/mekeor/nael ~/path/to/nael
@end example

In your Emacs initialization file, add entries to the @code{load-path} variable:

@lisp
(add-to-list 'load-path "~/path/to/nael/nael")
;; (add-to-list 'load-path "~/path/to/nael/nael-lsp")
;; (add-to-list 'load-path "~/path/to/nael/nael-markdown")
@end lisp

And load Nael:

@lisp
(require 'nael)
;; (require 'nael-lsp)
;; (require 'nael-markdown)
@end lisp

Optionally, configure Nael.

@node Via @code{use-package} and @samp{vc}
@section Via @code{use-package} and @samp{:vc}

@lisp
(use-package nael
  :vc ( :url "https://codeberg.org/mekeor/nael.git"
        :lisp-dir "nael"))
@end lisp

(Unfortunately, Emacs' built-in @code{package-vc} will byte-compile the Elisp source files of all packages inside Nael's Git repository. Please ignore the resulting compilation warnings.)

@node Usage
@chapter Usage

Language Server Protocol (LSP):

@itemize
@item
To start an LSP client automatically, configure @samp{nael-mode-hook}.  To start one interactively, type @samp{C-c C-e} (@code{eglot}), or, if you have installed @samp{nael-lsp}, @samp{C-c C-l} (@code{lsp}).

@item
@samp{C-h .} (@code{eldoc-doc-buffer}) displays the ElDoc documentation buffer showing tactic state and expected goal at point.
@end itemize

Abbreviations:

@itemize
@item
To enable abbreviations automatically, configure @code{nael-mode-hook}.  To enable them interactively, type @samp{C-c C-a} (@code{abbrev-mode}).

@item
@samp{C-c C-k} (@code{nael-abbrev-help}) will tell you how the abbreviation for the active region or character at point.

@item
Note that Nael's Abbrev tables use the @samp{:regexp} property which @uref{https://github.com/minad/cape/discussions/158#discussioncomment-14687758, is} neither compatible with Company nor Cape.  For completion at point, @samp{nael-abbrev} defines @code{nael-abbrev-capf} which is buffer-locally added to @code{completion-at-point-functions} whenever Abbrev mode is enabled inside Nael.  To ditch this CAPF, set the @code{nael-abbrev-capf} variable to @samp{nil}.
@end itemize

Emacs commands beyond Nael:

@itemize
@item
@samp{C-c C-c} or equally @samp{C-x p c} (@code{project-compile}) suggests @samp{lake build} as command to build the current project.
@item
@samp{M-g i} (@code{imenu}) jumps to a interactively chosen definition in current buffer.
@item
@samp{M-;} (@code{comment-dwim}) will toggle active region as comment or, if no region is active, create a comment at end of line.
@item
@samp{M-q} (@code{prog-fill-reindent-defun}) will fill the string- or comment-paragraph at point, or reindent the point-surrounding code.
@end itemize

